.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1476,2005]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1727,1752]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[280,453,1728,1752]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Syngnathidae" genus="Hippocampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Syngnathiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[280,453,1728,1752]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described from 
<collectingCountry box="[742,893,1727,1752]" name="New Zealand" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
New 
<collectingRegion box="[803,893,1727,1752]" country="Netherlands" name="Zeeland" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Zealand</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
and there is a question as to whether specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[212,315,1764,1789]" name="Australia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Australia</collectingCountry>
represent the same species. Studies that have addressed this question do not support the existence of multiple species based on morphological, meristic, and genetic data (357 bp, cyt 
<emphasis box="[1052,1066,1800,1824]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">b</emphasis>
) and show more variation within populations than among populations (Appendix 
<collectingRegion box="[702,725,1836,1860]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">A</collectingRegion>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Armstrong" box="[739,930,1836,1860]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Armstrong, P. (2001) Genetic and morphological variation in pot-bellied seahorses (Hippocampus abdominalis): is there evidence for two species? B. Sc. (Hons.) Thesis, School of Aquaculture, University of Tasmania." type="book" year="2001">Armstrong 2001</bibRefCitation>
). There is some genetic divergence between Australian and 
<collectingCountry box="[333,488,1871,1896]" name="New Zealand" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
New 
<collectingRegion box="[398,488,1871,1896]" country="Netherlands" name="Zeeland" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Zealand</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
populations (814bp cyt 
<emphasis box="[769,783,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">b</emphasis>
, 624bp CO1, 404bp CR, plus four microsatellite loci), however, the level of divergence (1.4–1.7%, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nickel" box="[662,933,1908,1933]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Nickel, J. &amp; Cursons, R. (2012) Genetic diversity and population structure of the pot-belly seahorse Hippocampus abdominalis in New Zealand. New Zealand Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research, 46, 207 - 218. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00288330.2011.632014" type="journal article" year="2012">Nickel &amp; Cursons 2012</bibRefCitation>
) is below our 2% threshold adopted for this revision. Divergence within 
<collectingCountry box="[482,637,1944,1969]" name="New Zealand" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
New 
<collectingRegion box="[547,637,1944,1969]" country="Netherlands" name="Zeeland" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Zealand</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
is 0.7–2.2% without any clear geographical structure (
<bibRefCitation author="Nickel" box="[1284,1431,1944,1969]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Nickel, J. E. (2009) The diversity of Hippocampus abdominalis in New Zealand. MSc thesis, The University of Waikato, Waikato, New Zealand." type="book" year="2009">Nickel 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nickel" box="[151,434,1980,2005]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Nickel, J. &amp; Cursons, R. (2012) Genetic diversity and population structure of the pot-belly seahorse Hippocampus abdominalis in New Zealand. New Zealand Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research, 46, 207 - 218. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00288330.2011.632014" type="journal article" year="2012">Nickel &amp; Cursons 2012</bibRefCitation>
). The name 
<taxonomicName box="[584,761,1980,2004]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Syngnathidae" genus="Hippocampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Syngnathiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[584,761,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
takes precedence with 
<taxonomicName box="[1040,1170,1981,2004]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Syngnathidae" genus="Hippocampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Syngnathiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agnesae">
<emphasis box="[1040,1170,1981,2004]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. agnesae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1233,1362,1980,2004]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Syngnathidae" genus="Hippocampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Syngnathiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bleekeri">
<emphasis box="[1233,1362,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. bleekeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being treated as synonyms. 
<taxonomicName box="[399,710,152,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Syngnathidae" genus="Hippocampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Syngnathiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="graciliformis">
<emphasis box="[399,710,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Hippocampus graciliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a juvenile specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1018,1192,152,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Syngnathidae" genus="Hippocampus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Syngnathiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[1018,1192,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">H. abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore is also synonymized.
</paragraph>
